'''Ethnophilosophy''' is the study of indigenous philosophical systems. The implicit concept is that a specific culture can have a [[philosophy]] that is not applicable and accessible to all peoples and cultures in the world; however, this concept is disputed by traditional philosophers. <ref> Samuel Oluoch Imbo, An Introduction to African Philosophy (1998), pp. 38-39, {{ISBN|0847688410}}</ref> An example of ethnophilosophy is [[African philosophy]].

